{
  "text": ". For each iteration, the complexity is dominated by the estimate of s and the projection of {q(\u03b8 k |Y)} k\u2208 S as D independent VM. According to [CITATION_1] , the calculation of s has complexity O(N K 3 ) and in general N = min d M d . For the projection operation, the complexity is O( KD 2 D d=1 M d + KD 3 ) which are mainly dominated by the calculation and inverse of Hessian matrix in (16b). Therefore, the computational estimation error is averaged over the trials in which K = K for a given simulation point. We define nominal signal-to-noise ratio (SNR) as SNR 10log( X 2 F / N 2 F ). The Algorithm stops when || X (t\u22121) \u2212 X (t) || F /|| X (t\u22121) || F < 10 \u22126 or t > 500, where t is the number of iterations.",
